This paper focuses on the problem of inferring the quality of questions and answers on a CQA website, specifically Stack Overflow, which is a platform for software-related questions. The paper proposes algorithms to predict the quality of both questions and answers, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which are all related to natural language processing and information retrieval. Additionally, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also likely sub-categories, as the paper involves machine learning techniques and analyzes the social network of Stack Overflow.
